summary: I remember GRRM once said something about how he took a good deal of inspiration for some of his favorite female characters in...
body: I remember GRRM once said something about how he took a good deal of inspiration for some of his favorite female characters in ASoIaF. When it came to mind, I immediately thought of Imogen from Cymbeline for Arya. She’s a righteous girl, loves her father, has to dress as man for a time bc she has to pose as a soldier, and I believe her younger brothers go missing as well. Also, she has a secret relationship with a man, Posthumus, who is a slightly lower class status then she is as a princess heir. Ultimately, she marries him even though she believes him dead for a time (I think the word posthumous is derived from this play?) and it’s in large part because he’s actually the son of a god lol don’t ask it’s a romance.

summary: Maisie Williams: It's been a very long time since the two of them have seen each other and she feels like an extremely different...
body:
Maisie Williams: It’s been a very long time since the two of them have seen each other and she feels like an extremely different person. She almost finds it as a bit of an escape.

Joe Dempsie: I think he’s fascinated by her. It’s the attraction that surprises him more than anything.

Maisie Williams: I think it really is a coming-of-age moment for Arya.

Joe Dempsie: Gendry’s just kind of bamboozled by the scenario and before he know it, you know, it’s all happening.

Maisie Williams: Everyone believes that this could be it. As a woman, I think she ought to know what it’s like. [laugh]

Source: Game of Thrones | Season 8 Episode 2 | The Last Night (HBO)
